{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_73","type":"agent_message","text":"The native probe isolates the problem: the service root exists in the image, but native `ClassLoader.getResources(...)` returns a `resource:/...` URL, and Camel’s scanner doesn’t know how to walk that protocol as a jar or directory. That means the remaining test failure is caused by Camel’s scan implementation, not by missing file/constructor metadata anymore. I’m checking one last detail: what the `resource:/.../health-check/` stream actually contains, in case there’s a metadata-only way to feed the scanner a usable listing."}}
